      "span_text": "A version of this problem was in fact also considered by Papapetrou, first for linear (electromagnetic) fields and partially for the gravitational field [CITATION_1] , who argued that if a solution is stationary in the past of a characteristic hypersurface, and non-radiative towards the future, then it should be stationary everywhere.",
